Commix
Automated command injection exploitation tool

Web Application
Description
Commix (Command Injection Exploiter) is an automated tool for testing and exploiting command injection vulnerabilities in web applications.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which commix
Install command:

sudo apt install commix
Basic Syntax
commix -u "<URL>"
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
commix -u "http://target.com/page?cmd=test"

Basic test	Test for command injection	
commix -u "http://target.com/page?cmd=test" --os-cmd=whoami

Execute command	Run system command	
commix -u "http://target.com/page?cmd=test" --all

All techniques	Try all injection methods	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Identify potential injection point
2
Run commix with URL
3
Review if vulnerable
4
If exploitable, get shell access
5
Document findings
Understanding the Output
Shows if parameter is injectable. Provides shell access if successful.

Important Warnings
•
Command injection is severe
•
Can lead to full system access
•
Only test authorized targets
•
Highly illegal without permission
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
